kind: knowledge
title: voit/loop
---

# voit/loop

```
ramble  ->  vision (main)                    tend vision, review, merge
              |
   small? ----+----  /tweak <task>           unrestricted worktree, straight to main
              |
   slice? --- /organize <slice>              organizer worktree, plans in voit-memory
                       |
                       /dispatch <task>  ...  worker worktrees, write the code
                       |
                       /promote <branch> ...  worker -> slice   (review gate)
              |
   /promote <slice>                          slice  -> main    (review gate)
```

- The branch name sets the role: `organize-*`, `implement-*`, `tweak-*`, else
  vision on the root checkout.
- The diagram is one slice's path, not a queue: many organizers (and their workers)
  run at once, each in its own worktree on its own branch. Concurrency is the design -
  vision opens slices as they arise and never serializes one organizer behind another.
  The lone exception is a structural dependency: a slice that reshapes a foundation
  later slices build on is landed first (foundation-freeze, see `voit/vision`) - ordering
  a real dependency, never independent work.
- Each `/promote` runs `voit/review` on the diff. Nothing reaches `main` unreviewed.
- Every session auto-registers on the bus at SessionStart (the `role-scope` hook;
  id = `vision` on `main`, else the branch name). The roster is who's live.
- Coordinate over the bus - one long-lived daemon every agent JOINs over
  `.voitbus.sock` (an `AF_UNIX` socket at the vision-tree root, lazily started by the
  first client, state snapshotted to `.voitbus.json` so a restart keeps unread mail),
  via either the `bus_*` MCP tools (the `bus` server) or `python3 .voit/scripts/bus.py`.
  Address an explicit id, `*`, or a logical `up` / `vision` / `my-organizer` the
  daemon resolves from lineage. Workers post `ready:` to their organizer (`up`),
  organizers post `ready:organize-<slice>` to `vision`. Receiving is always the same
  move: background `bus.py watch <self> [match]` - the daemon pushes the match the
  instant it arrives and the harness re-invokes you; never poll. (`watch` stays
  CLI-only: a blocking wait does not fit one MCP call.)
- Questions use `ask`/`reply`: the asker runs `bus.py ask <self> <to> "<q>"`, gets a
  correlation token, and backgrounds `watch <self> reply:<token>` - so it wakes on
  exactly its own answer even with several asks in flight.
- Two bus hooks run automatically (id from `.claude/busid`, written by the role
  hook): `UserPromptSubmit` peeks your unread messages and surfaces them each turn,
  non-destructive - `bus read` still consumes; `Stop` runs `bus gc`, dropping
  expired agents and any message its recipient has already read. The peek surfaces
  what is waiting; `watch` is still how you wake on arrival while stopped.
- Worktrees are created with worktrunk (`wt switch --create --no-cd`), which maps each
  branch to `.worktrees/<branch>` - VOIT's existing layout. `/organize`, `/dispatch` and
  `/tweak` all launch their child as a **visible in-session subagent** via the Agent tool
  (`subagent_type voit:organizer` / `voit:worker` / `voit:tweak`; `/dispatch` forks off
  your HEAD with `--base @`), confined by the write-scope hook (tweak gets no scope -
  unrestricted by design): the child reports `ready:` over the bus AND its final message
  lands in your session - no human open step, never tell the user to open a terminal. The
  headless detached alternative for a child is `claude --bg ... --agent voit:<role>`
  (survives the terminal closing); reconnect with `claude attach <id>` (Ctrl+Z detaches,
  it keeps running), peek with `claude logs <id>`, list with `claude agents`, end with
  `claude stop <id>`.
- `/promote` merges after the review gate passes. Vision on the root checkout uses
  `wt merge` (lands the child worktree's branch into the target and removes the
  worktree); an organizer folding INSIDE its own worktree uses plain `git merge` -
  `wt merge` run from a worktree can remove the runner's own worktree (see
  `/promote`). The gate is unchanged - nothing reaches `main` unreviewed.
- The main session on `main` defaults to the **vision** agent
  (`"agent": "voit:vision"` in settings).
